        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1636846571" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5096991707280736023">I wish Goodreads allowed you to give a book six stars. This is the best novel I have read in years. It required a bit of concentration at first but once I realised what was happening (the clue is in the title) I was hooked. It took a while to read but that was only because it was so rich, I didn&apos;t want to miss a thing. By the end I was flying through faster than I would have liked. <i>Conversation in The Cathedral</i> is a book about life, as the best books always are, told in the way life is told. Hal</span>
  <span id="freeText5096991707280736023" style="display:none">I wish Goodreads allowed you to give a book six stars. This is the best novel I have read in years. It required a bit of concentration at first but once I realised what was happening (the clue is in the title) I was hooked. It took a while to read but that was only because it was so rich, I didn't want to miss a thing. By the end I was flying through faster than I would have liked. <i>Conversation in The Cathedral</i> is a book about life, as the best books always are, told in the way life is told. Half of me feels this style would appeal more to women, given our habit of discussing a million things at once, but given that Vargas Llosa himself said, "If I could only save from a fire one of the novels I've written, I would save this one," it's probably just universally brilliant.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5096991707280736023" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
