        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer7038907" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2158626442305723344">MVL was obviously heavily influenced by the stream-of-consciousness style of Faulkner. I prefer his work over Faulkner&apos;s any day and especially this novel. It has much more to say about society than the work of most writers. It&apos;s not just some sort of creative writing exercise, it is a portrait of Peruvian politics and culture from the era of Odría. Like some of his other early work, it is also a novel about Lima.</span>
  <span id="freeText2158626442305723344" style="display:none">MVL was obviously heavily influenced by the stream-of-consciousness style of Faulkner. I prefer his work over Faulkner's any day and especially this novel. It has much more to say about society than the work of most writers. It's not just some sort of creative writing exercise, it is a portrait of Peruvian politics and culture from the era of Odría. Like some of his other early work, it is also a novel about Lima.</span>
