<div id="review_931322852" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/931322852" />
    <a title="Vasi Maier" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/16570207-vasi-maier"><img alt="Vasi Maier" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1358536489p2/16570207.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/931322852?book_show_action=true">May 08, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Vasi Maier" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Vasi Maier" href="/user/show/16570207-vasi-maier">Vasi Maier</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer931322852" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4009598237362250370">absolutely impressed. <br/>i feel i need to brake this down into: how i tried, couldn&apos;t, wouldn&apos;t even want to pick it up again..basically hating the first 400pages,but then breaking through, to the &quot;other side&quot;, from where all things seem clear, logical. <br/><br/>it is a difficult read. it&apos;s the unpolished Llosa, clearly an earlier attempt at his intricate story weaving style. <br/><br/>what does strike me: he tells you from the start, from the first moment a new character appears what is going to happen to him, and t</span>
  <span id="freeText4009598237362250370" style="display:none">absolutely impressed. <br />i feel i need to brake this down into: how i tried, couldn't, wouldn't even want to pick it up again..basically hating the first 400pages,but then breaking through, to the "other side", from where all things seem clear, logical. <br /><br />it is a difficult read. it's the unpolished Llosa, clearly an earlier attempt at his intricate story weaving style. <br /><br />what does strike me: he tells you from the start, from the first moment a new character appears what is going to happen to him, and then he makes you live with them for 500-600 pages. he makes you feel sad when they eventually disappear. they are all awful, yet good in their own struggles. i cannot find one negative character in the entire book. <br /><br />monumental work. towards the end, i didn't want the book to finish.</span>
  <a data-text-id="4009598237362250370" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


